This paper deals with the problem of registering LiDAR scans, which is a fundamental problem in 3D mapping and robotic navigation. The paper proposes a new algorithm for this task, which involves the use of a geometric metric called Transformation Compatibility Measure (TCM). This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with large-scale urban modeling applications, which suggests that it may also belong to the graphics (cs.GR) and computer graphics (cs.CG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes an optimization technique using gradient descent and simulated annealing, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
